<TITLE> NBR extends tax-return deadline to Oct 31 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 24 (bdnews24.com) - The deadline for income tax returns filings in the individual category has been extended by one month to Oct 31, the National Board of Revenue said in a statement Monday. NBR chairman Badiur Rahman, explaining the time extension told reporters: "It was in response to the demand of different quarters and organisations. Besides, the Ramadan and the floods have also been taken into consideration." The NBR statement said the time extension would also apply to self-assessed taxpayers in the individual category. The statement requested all taxpayers to submit their income tax returns for tax year 2007-08 by the deadline. In line with rules, those who earn Tk 1.5 lakh or more a year are liable to pay income tax. bdnews
